text: Bro this is nothing compared to the engine braking that the MGU-K in modern F1 cars have. And far far more efficient in recouping the power that would otherwise be wasted in kinetic energy. Not to mention the MGU-H which further helps the car‚Äôs battery pack to charge. The engine braking if turned up on an F1 cars almost could rip your eyes out your head! But it‚Äôs rarely turned up to that level as teams all use different engines maps which all have different regeneration levels, to be as quick as possible in different circuit layouts and different fuel loads during the race as the car keeps on getting lighter and lighter as it burns fuel throughout the race.
author: @Hassannnnnnnn

text:
¬†@Hassannnnnnnn¬† We shouldn't be comparing F1 cars to electric motorcycles to begin with.. both are purpose built machines.
but if we are.. 
F1 specs - the maximum power output of the MGU-K is 120 kW (of the 650 kW vehicle's max power - that's 24% power recovery). 
By comparison the F77 Mach2 can regenerate 30% of peak power - as told during the launch
The maximum battery storage allowed on an F1 car is 4 MJ (1.1kWh) - that's 1/10th of the UV battery pack of 10kWh which can store a lot more recovered kinetic energy..
